AU  - G. Wan
AU  - M. Wang
AU  - T. Wang
AU  - M. Huang
AU  - L. Lu
AU  - Z. Yang
T2  - 2025 8th International Conference on Transportation Information and Safety (ICTIS)
AB  - In ship driving and remote control, the use of automatic identification system (AIS) and shipborne cameras can realize the functions of target ship information labeling, enhanced perception under low visibility, and risk warning, so it has become a hot topic of current research. This paper proposes a ship target detection and tracking algorithm suitable for complex dynamic environment, which fuses text and video information through multi-modality. Firstly, we propose a new AIS trajectory generation algorithm, which combines wide-area information search and high-precision track prediction. Secondly, we propose a target ship video information trajectory projection method based on YOLOv5 network and DeepSORT algorithm. Finally, we use the asynchronous trajectory matching method to fuse the trajectories matched by AIS and video data to achieve real-time high-precision matching of ship targets. Experimental results show that the average recognition accuracy of the proposed algorithm reaches 84.40%, and the average recall rate reaches 72.5%. Compared with the Faster R-CNN, SSD and YOLOv8 algorithms, the proposed algorithm improves the average recognition accuracy by 187%, 14% and 5.9%, respectively, and the average recall rate by 42.1%, 664.7% and 4.0%, respectively, and the multi-target tracking accuracy is improved by 45% compared with the SORT algorithm. The algorithm has high detection accuracy and plays an active role in ensuring the safety of ships.
