AU  - X. Yang
AU  - J. Xu
AU  - J. Lan
AU  - Y. Zhou
AU  - X. Chu
T2  - 2025 8th International Conference on Transportation Information and Safety (ICTIS)
AB  - With the rapid increase in cross-river and cross-sea bridges, the risk of ship-bridge collisions has become increasingly severe. To effectively address this issue, this study proposed a novel active bridge collision prevention warning system. The system integrated multiple sensors, including the automatic identification system (AIS), maritime radar, LiDAR, ultrasonic water level sensors, and cameras, and applied advanced data processing methods for AIS, radar imagery, and LiDAR, along with multi-source data fusion techniques. It enabled high-precision identification of key parameters such as ship speed, trajectory, and height. The system was designed with early warning functions for abnormal conditions such as excessive height, overspeeding, and yawing. Practical applications have demonstrated that the system provides all-weather, around-the-clock, and fully automated bridge safety protection and early warning, significantly reducing the risk of ship-bridge collisions.
