TY  - CONF
TI  - Throughput Prediction of Chongqing Inland Port Based on Time Series Decomposition and Integrated Machine Learning Method
AU  - H. Mei
T2  - 2024 International Conference on Telecommunications and Power Electronics (TELEPE)
AB  - The purpose of this study is to improve the ability to accurately predict the throughput of inland ports in Chongqing. By combining the application of time series decomposition and integrated Machine Learning (ML) method, the internal structure and complex relationship of port throughput data are deeply explored. Through the seasonality and trend revealed in time series decomposition and the importance of features mined in integrated ML model, this study has realized a comprehensive understanding and efficient prediction of port throughput. Firstly, through time series decomposition, this study reveals the seasonal and trend patterns in port throughput data. The trend component clearly shows the long-term growth trend of port throughput, which provides a reliable reference for future planning. The discovery of seasonal components enables us to better understand the periodic fluctuation of throughput in different time periods, which provides an opportunity for resource allocation and operation optimization. Secondly, the integrated ML methods, such as Random forest (RF) and gradient lifting, are used to successfully capture the nonlinear relationships and complex patterns in throughput data. Through the comprehensive application of the model, this study has achieved high prediction accuracy. The model evaluation results show that the selected integrated ML method performs well in port throughput prediction and has a wide application prospect. The comprehensive application of time series decomposition and integrated ML method in this study provides an innovative method for the accurate prediction of Chongqing inland port throughput. This research has important practical significance in the field of port management and planning.
