AU  - R. S. Azzam
AU  - H. Hassan Ghazal
AU  - M. S. Gheith
T2  - 2025 7th Novel Intelligent and Leading Emerging Sciences Conference (NILES)
AB  - This study develops a multi-objective optimization model for Truck Appointment Systems (TAS) in container terminals, explicitly integrating truck turnaround time (TTT) considerations. Using integer programming and the lexicographic method, the model minimizes deviations between preferred and assigned truck arrival windows while reducing congestion and optimizing terminal resource utilization. The approach accounts for terminal capacity, crane productivity, yard distances, and dynamic scheduling factors. Computational experiments under realistic scenarios demonstrate substantial reductions in TTT and improved workload distribution, enhancing terminal efficiency. The model is scalable across diverse operational contexts. Future research directions include stochastic modeling of truck arrivals, real-time data integration, and environmental impact assessment.
