AB  - Smart cities depend on cross-domain data exchange, yet its effectiveness is limited by semantic heterogeneity and privacy-induced information asymmetry, which complicate traditional integration. Although ontology alignment can resolve semantic disparities, it struggles under incomplete knowledge conditions. Leveraging the emergent capabilities of Large Language Models (LLMs), this paper introduces an LLM-centric, task-oriented paradigm that automates ontology alignment and enables data exchange under realistic constraints. A case study demonstrates the approach's practicality in facilitating semantic interoperability without full information disclosure, highlighting its potential for privacy-aware smart city applications.
