AB  - IntruSafe, an innovative secure messaging platform that is designed to protect against Man-in-the-Middle (MITM) attacks and other such security threats is what this paper introduces. With end to end encryption and confidentiality, integrity and authenticity, IntruSafe integrates advanced techniques such as RSA for key exchange, AES for end to end encryption, SHA-256 hashing and ECDSA digital signatures. The platform is equipped with its Intrusion Detection System (IDS) powered by ML which detects attacks using Random Forest algorithm and prevents them in real time for all kinds of attacks DoS controlling, DDoS, Port Scanning etc. With the help of a combination of cryptographic protocols along with machine learning, IntruSafe provides better security, higher performance, and scalable communication and is the solution of choice for high risk settings including enterprise network and lOT systems. IntruSafe's operational framework, technical specifications and capability to counter evolving cybersecurity threats in a modern messaging environment is outlined in this paper.
