AB  - With continuous breakthroughs in computer technology, time series data classification is becoming increasingly widely used in robotics, artificial intelligence, automation, and intelligent control. However, in practical applications, classification models often require significant time for parameter tuning and testing. In this work, we propose and design a data fusion method based on multi-scale segmentation reconstruction for time series data classification. This method aims to enhance the features of the original time series data and implicitly reduce noise by fusing reconstructed time series from reconstruction methods. It also accelerates model learning efficiency using default parameters. We tested this method on UCR public datasets and classic classification models. The results show that the proposed method effectively improves model convergence speed and accuracy.
