TI  - TriRoute: Low-Latency 1x3 Router for Optimized Data Distribution
AU  - S. S
AU  - R. R. Ramakrishnan
AU  - R. Singh
AU  - R. G. R
AU  - N. Gupta
T2  - 2025 7th International Conference on Inventive Material Science and Applications (ICIMA)
AB  - To provide low latency and efficient data distribution in high-speed communication networks, packet routing must be done well. A low latency 1x3 router that can route data packets from a single source to any of three output ports based on the destination address is designed and implemented in this project. [1] Major features like packet routing, error-detection parity checking, reset action, and effective packet transmission and reception techniques are all included in the router's architecture. To provide excellent performance and dependability, the planned router is built using FPGA-based verification methodologies and hardware description languages (HDLs). While the reset mechanism guarantees system stability and fault recovery, parity checking is integrated to detect transmission defects and preserve data integrity. [2] The router's low latency, high throughput, and efficient packet management make it suitable for network-on-chip (NoC) architectures, FPGA-based systems, and real-time data transmission systems, according to performance analysis conducted through simulation and hardware implementation. In order to make it more relevant in high-performance computing and embedded system applications, future developments will include scalability to support additional output ports, advanced error correction algorithms, and power-efficient design methodologies. The design of robust, dependable, and fast routing designs for modern processing and communication systems is advanced by this research.
