TY  - CONF
TI  - Ship AIS Trajectory Outlier Identification Model under High-speed Sampling Conditions
AU  - H. Wang
AU  - Q. Chen
T2  - 2024 4th International Symposium on Computer Technology and Information Science (ISCTIS)
AB  - In order to efficiently identify the outliers of ship AIS trajectories under high-speed sampling conditions, this paper proposes an outlier identification model based on ship position distance distribution. Taking the ship AIS track data of Yangshan port as an example, the kernel density is used to estimate the daily ship position distance distribution, and then the threshold is determined and the outliers are screened out. In this paper, it is proved that the ship position distance distributions on two adjacent days are approximate, so the threshold value of yesterday can be substituted into today to identify today’s outliers effectively. The experimental results show that in the application environments of Yangshan Port waters where the average rate of ship AIS track data writing into the database is 43 items/sec and the coastal waters of East China Sea where the average rate of ship AIS track data writing into the database is 287 items/sec, the model is able to efficiently identify the outliers of the ship AIS trajectories.
